    "In this experiment, we repeat the calculations for three different data splits and five different random seeds to make the results less prone to random noise, e.g.",
    "due to the random weight initialization.",
    "We find that all components, including the distance matrix, are crucial for achieving optimal performance of R-MAT.",
    "The use of all information sources results in the best performance across all tested datasets.",
    "The performance for the smallest FreeSolv dataset is considerably better when more information sources are included."
